-- Chairman of South Africa's HCI steps down - e-mail
-- By David Dolan
-- Mon Oct 27, 2014 10:18AM EDT
-- None



JOHANNESBURG, Oct 27 (Reuters) - The executive chairman of South Africa's Hosken Consolidated Investments <HCIJ.J> has resigned, he said in an e-mail to staff on Monday, citing an "intolerable" relationship with the board of the investment firm.

